-- OBSERVATIONS
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

⊢= obs-fast-convergence
  given §16-evolution-simulator
  yield observations

  ⊢= observations ← "SINGLE-GENERATION CONVERGENCE REVEALS STRONG SEEDING: The ⊢∘ evolve loop exited after just 1 iteration (of 4 allowed). The initial seed-population had mean fitness 7.67 — already high because the ∴ prompt was well-specified (name, audience, constraints, emotional targets). One round of tournament selection + crossover + mutation pushed the mean to 8.33, clearing the ≥8 threshold. This is NOT a failure of the evolution mechanism — it's evidence that the brief cell provided enough constraint to guide the LLM toward strong initial candidates. In a weaker brief (e.g., 'make a coffee logo'), more iterations would be needed."

⊢= obs-replace-semantics
  given §16-evolution-simulator
  yield observations

  ⊢= observations ← "REPLACE SEMANTICS ARE CORRECT FOR GENETIC ALGORITHMS: The ⊢∘ evolve loop uses 'replace' (not 'accumulate'). Each generation REPLACES the previous population — you don't want generation N's candidates competing with generation N+1's in the fitness evaluation. This is the standard GA model: a fixed-size population where selection pressure drives improvement. Accumulate semantics would produce a growing candidate pool, which is the wrong model for tournament selection. The v0.2 explicit accumulate/replace annotation makes this intention visible in the program text."

⊢= obs-guard-dispatch-clean
  given §16-evolution-simulator
  yield observations

  ⊢= observations ← "GUARD CLAUSES ENABLE PROPER CONVERGENCE VS STAGNATION DISPATCH: R16 had a single ⊢∘ loop that exited on EITHER high fitness OR stagnation, with no way to distinguish the two exit conditions downstream. v0.2 guard clauses split the post-loop handling: convergence-report (where new-mean-fitness ≥ 8) celebrates the winner, stagnation-report (where new-mean-fitness < 8) diagnoses failure. Both share 'where converged = true' — they only activate after the loop exits. Exactly one fires. The other's yields become ⊥. No wasted LLM evaluation on the irrelevant path."

⊢= obs-aspirational-oracles
  given §16-evolution-simulator
  yield observations

  ⊢= observations ← "ASPIRATIONAL ORACLES ON seed-population ARE THE RIGHT CALL: The seed-population cell has 4 oracles (count, description fields, uniqueness, constraints). Under v0.2, these are ASPIRATIONAL because seed-population is ⊢∘-managed. If the LLM generates only 5 candidates instead of 6, the oracle '⊨ candidates has exactly 6 entries' fails — but the cell still freezes and the evolution loop continues. The oracle failure feeds back through evaluate-fitness → select-and-crossover → judge-generation, creating pressure toward the right output without hard-blocking the loop. The loop's 'until converged = true' is the actual gate."

⊢= obs-given-optional-bootstrap
  given §16-evolution-simulator
  yield observations

  ⊢= observations ← "given? ON mean-fitness HANDLES THE BOOTSTRAP EDGE: judge-generation uses 'given? evaluate-fitness→mean-fitness' because in a hypothetical alternate wiring where evaluate-fitness runs INSIDE the loop (not as a pre-loop step), the first iteration would have no prior mean-fitness. The given? makes judge-generation tolerant of that ⊥ case — it would set converged=false and let the loop continue. In THIS execution, evaluate-fitness ran pre-loop so the value was available, but the given? makes the cell robust to rewiring."

⊢= obs-crossover-is-semantic
  given §16-evolution-simulator
  yield observations

  ⊢= observations ← "CROSSOVER IS SEMANTIC, NOT SYNTACTIC: The select-and-crossover cell performs genetic crossover via natural language instruction — 'visual from parent 1, typography from parent 2'. This is fundamentally different from traditional GA crossover (bit-flipping, subtree swap). The LLM understands the MEANING of each trait and combines them coherently. The result (Geometric Titan = Titan's figure + Monogram's typography) is a genuine synthesis, not a random splice. This is the semantic computation substrate earning its keep — crossover that understands what it's crossing."

⊢= obs-file-scope-recovery-net
  given §16-evolution-simulator
  yield observations

  ⊢= observations ← "FILE-SCOPE ⊨? PROVIDES DEFENSE IN DEPTH: The file-scope recovery policy (retry max 2, exhaustion → error-value(⊥)) applies to any cell without its own ⊨?. If evaluate-fitness produces rankings that aren't a valid permutation, the file-scope ⊨? catches it and retries with feedback. Inside the ⊢∘ loop, oracles are aspirational so the file-scope policy doesn't override — but for pre-loop and post-loop cells (brief, convergence-report), the file-scope ⊨? is the only safety net. One declaration covers the whole file. Defense in depth."
